1 AN ACT relating to the Kentucky Child Mental Health Services Access Program.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS 210.370 TO 210.485 IS CREATED
4 TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) The Kentucky Child Mental Health Services Access Program is hereby
6 established. The purpose of the program shall be to help health care practitioners
7 in the Commonwealth meet the needs of a child with mental illness or a child
8 with an intellectual disability.
9 (2) The program shall be operated by each regional community services program for
10 mental health or individuals with an intellectual disability established pursuant to
11 KRS 210.370.
12 (3) The program shall at a minimum employ a psychiatrist licensed pursuant to KRS
13 Chapter 311 and a psychologist licensed pursuant to KRS Chapter 319.
14 (4) The program shall operate a dedicated hotline phone number Monday through
15 Friday from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. local time that serves as the entry point to the
16 program for health care practitioners to be able to get services for a child with
17 mental illness or a child with an intellectual disability. Services may include:
18 (a) Immediate clinical consultation over the telephone;
19 (b) Expedited face-to-face mental health consultation;
20 (c) Care coordination for assistance with referrals to community behavioral
21 health services; and
22 (d) Continuing professional education specifically designed for health care
23 practitioners.
24 Section 2. KRS 210.400 is amended to read as follows:
25 Subject to the provisions of this section and the policies and regulations of the secretary
26 of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services, each community board for mental health
27 or individuals with an intellectual disability shall:
